3. Data Handling
-----------------
PanicBase processes panic logs and device data locally on the End User's
machine. The application does not transmit panic logs, IMEI, UDID, serial
numbers, Apple ID, photographs, or any user-identifying data to PanicBase
servers or any third-party server. Personally identifying markers are
redacted before local storage. All persisted records are encrypted at rest
using ChaCha20-Poly1305 with a per-machine random key held in the operating
system credential store.

4. iCloud and Apple Services
-----------------------------
The application may connect to Apple Inc. servers ("iCloud") solely on
behalf of the End User and only using credentials the End User explicitly
provides through the embedded Apple authentication web view. PanicBase does
not store, log, or transmit Apple ID credentials. Session cookies remain
within the operating system web view cookie store and may be cleared at
any time by the End User via the in-app sign-out action.

